			-
				-
					Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 1
				-
					-
						Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 1: Line 1
					-
						-
							Thou, Agni, wast the earliest Angiras, a Seer; thou wast, a God
							thyself, the Gods' auspicious Friend.
						-
					-
						Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 1: Line 2
					-
						-
							After thy holy ordinance the Maruts, sage, active through wisdom, with
							their glittering spears, were born.
						-
				-
					Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							O Agni, thou, the best and earliest Angiras, fulfillest as a Sage the
							holy law of Gods.
						-
					-
						Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							Sprung from two mothers, wise, through all existence spread, resting in
							many a place for sake of living man.
						-
				-
					Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 3
				-
					-
						Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 3: Line 1
					-
						-
							To Matarisvan first thou, Agni, wast disclosed, and to Vivasvan through
							thy noble inward power.
						-
					-
						Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 3: Line 2
					-
						-
							Heaven and Earth, Vasu! shook at the choosing of the Priest: the
							burthen thou didst bear, didst worship mighty Gods.
						-
				-
					Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 4
				-
					-
						Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 4: Line 1
					-
						-
							Agni thou madest heaven to thunder for mankind; thou, yet more pious,
							for pious Pururavas.
						-
					-
						Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 4: Line 2
					-
						-
							When thou art rapidly freed from thy parents, first eastward they bear
							thee round, and, after, to the west.
						-
				-
					Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 5
				-
					-
						Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 5: Line 1
					-
						-
							Thou, Agni, art a Bull who makes our store increase, to be invoked by
							him who lifts the ladle up.
						-
					-
						Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 5: Line 2
					-
						-
							Well knowing the oblation with the hallowing word, uniting all who
							live, thou lightenest first our folk
						-
				-
					Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 6
				-
					-
						Mandala 1: Hymn 31: Verse 6: Line 1
					-
						-
							Agni, thou savest in the synod when pursued e'en him, farseeing One!
