							when thou protectest.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 11: Verse 6: Line 2
					-
						-
							Son of Strength, Agni, blest is he at evening, whom thou as God
							attendest for his welfare.
						-
			-
				Mandala 4: Hymn 12
			-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 1
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 1: Line 1
					-
						-
							WHOSO enkindles thee, with lifted ladle, and thrice this day offiers
							thee food, O Agni,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 1: Line 2
					-
						-
							May he excel, triumphant through thy splendours, wise through thy
							mental power, O Jatavedas.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							Whoso with toil and trouble brings thee fuel, serving the majesty of
							mighty Agni,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							He, kindling thee at evening and at morning, prospers, and comes to
							wealth, and slays his foemen.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 3
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 3: Line 1
					-
						-
							Agni is Master of sublime dominion, Agni is Lord of strength and lofty
							riches.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 3: Line 2
					-
						-
							Straightway the self-reliant God, Most Youthful, gives treasures to the
							mortal who adores him.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 4
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 4: Line 1
					-
						-
							Most Youthful God, whatever sin, through folly, we here, as human
							beings, have committed,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 4: Line 2
					-
						-
							In sight of Aditi make thou us sinless remit, entirely, Agni, our
							offences.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 5
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 5: Line 1
					-
						-
							Even in the presence of great sin, O Agni, free us from prison of the
							Gods or mortals.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 5: Line 2
					-
						-
							Never may we who are thy friends be injured: grant health and strength
							unto our seed and offspring.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 6
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 6: Line 1
					-
						-
							Even as ye here, Gods Excellent and Holy, have loosed the cow that by
							the foot was tethered,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 12: Verse 6: Line 2
					-
						-
							So also set us free from this affliction long let our life, O Agni, be
							extended.
						-
			-
				Mandala 4: Hymn 13
			-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 13: Verse 1
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 13: Verse 1: Line 1
					-
						-
							AGNI hath looked, benevolently-minded, on the wealth-giving spring of
							radiant Mornings.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 13: Verse 1: Line 2
					-
						-
							Come, Asvins, to the dwelling of the pious: Surya the God is rising
							with his splendour.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 13: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 13: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							Savitar, God, hath spread on high his lustre, waving his flag like a
							spoil-seeking hero.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 13: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							Their stablished way go Varuna and Mitra, what time they make the Sun
							ascend the heaven.
						-
