					Mandala 4: Hymn 16: Verse 10
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 16: Verse 10: Line 1
					-
						-
							Come to our home resolved to slay the Dasyu: Kutsa longed eagerly to
							win thy friendship.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 16: Verse 10: Line 2
					-
						-
							Alike in form ye both sate in his dwelling the faithful Lady was in
							doubt between you.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 16: Verse 11
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 16: Verse 11: Line 1
					-
						-
							Thou comest, fain to succour him, with Kutsa,-a goad that masters both
							the Wind-God's horses,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 16: Verse 11: Line 2
					-
						-
							That, holding the brown steeds like spoil for capture, the sage may on
							the final day be present.
						-
