				Mandala 4: Hymn 24
			-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 1
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 1: Line 1
					-
						-
							WHAT worthy praise will bring before us Indra, the Son of Strength,
							that he may grant us riches;
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 1: Line 2
					-
						-
							For he the Hero, gives the singer treasures: he is the Lord who sends
							us gifts, ye people.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							To be invoked and hymned in fight with Vrtra, that well-praised Indra
							gives us real bounties.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							That Maghavan brings comfort in the foray to the religious man who
							pours libations.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 3
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 3: Line 1
					-
						-
							Him, verily, the men invoke in combat; risking their lives they make
							him their protector,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 3: Line 2
					-
						-
							When heroes, foe to foe, give up their bodies, fighting, each side, for
							children and their offspring.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 4
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 4: Line 1
					-
						-
							Strong God! the folk at need put forth their vigour, striving together
							in the whirl of battle.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 4: Line 2
					-
						-
							When warrior bands encounter one another some in the grapple quit
							themselves like Indra.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 5
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 5: Line 1
					-
						-
							Hence many a one worships the might of Indra: hence let the brew
							succeed the meal-oblation.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 5: Line 2
					-
						-
							Hence let the Soma banish those who pour not: even hence I joy to pay
							the Strong One worship.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 6
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 6: Line 1
					-
						-
							Indra gives comfort to the man who truly presses, for him who longs fot
							it, the Soma,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 6: Line 2
					-
						-
							Not disaffected, with devoted spirit this man he takes to be his friend
							in battles.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 7
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 7: Line 1
					-
						-
							He who this day for Indra presses Soma, prepares the brew and fries the
							grains of barley-
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 7: Line 2
					-
						-
							Loving the hymns of that devoted servant, to him may Indra give heroic
							vigour.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 8
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 8: Line 1
					-
						-
							When the impetuous chief hath sought the confliet, and the lord looked
							upon the long-drawn battle,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 24: Verse 8: Line 2
					-
						-
							The matron calls to the Strong God whom pressers of Soma have
							encouraged int the dwelling.
						-
