				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 11
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 11: Line 1
					-
						-
							So there this car of Usas lay, broken to pieces, in Vipas,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 11: Line 2
					-
						-
							And she herself fled far away.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 12
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 12: Line 1
					-
						-
							Thou, Indra, didst. with magic power resist the overflowing stream
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 12: Line 2
					-
						-
							Who spread her waters o'er the land.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 13
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 13: Line 1
					-
						-
							Valiantly didst thou seize and take the store which Susna had amassed,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 13: Line 2
					-
						-
							When thou didst crush his fortresses.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 14
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 14: Line 1
					-
						-
							Thou, Indra, also smotest down Kulitara's son Sambara,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 30: Verse 14: Line 2
					-
						-
