							From inmost reservoir in countless channels flow down these rivers
							which the foe beholds not.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 5: Line 2
					-
						-
							I look upon the streams of oil descending, and lo! the Golden Reed is
							there among them.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 6
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 6: Line 1
					-
						-
							Like rivers our libations flow together, cleansing themselves in inmost
							heart and spirit.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 6: Line 2
					-
						-
							The streams of holy oil pour swiftly downward like the wild beasts that
							fly before the bowman.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 7
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 7: Line 1
					-
						-
							As rushing down the rapids of a river, flow swifter than the wind the
							vigorous currents,
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 7: Line 2
					-
						-
							The streams of oil in swelling fluctuation like a red courser bursting
							through the fences.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 8
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 8: Line 1
					-
						-
							women at a gathering fair to look on and gently smiling, they incline
							to Agni.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 8: Line 2
					-
						-
							The streams of holy oil attain the fuel, and Jatavedas joyfully
							receives them.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 9
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 9: Line 1
					-
						-
							As maidens dock themselves with gay adornment to join the bridal feast,
							I now behold them.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 9: Line 2
					-
						-
							Where Soma flows and sacrifice is ready, thither the streams of holy
							oil are running.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 10
				-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 10: Line 1
					-
						-
							Send to our eulogy a herd of cattle bestow upon us excellent
							possessions.
						-
					-
						Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 10: Line 2
					-
						-
							Bear to the Gods the sacrifice we offer the streams of oil flow pure
							and full of sweetness.
						-
				-
					Mandala 4: Hymn 58: Verse 11
				-
					-
						The universe depends upon thy power and might within the sea, within the
						heart, within all life.
					-
		-
			Mandala 5
		-
