					Mandala 5: Hymn 2: Verse 7
				-
					-
						Mandala 5: Hymn 2: Verse 7: Line 1
					-
						-
							Thou from the stake didst loose e'en Sunahsepa bound for a thousand;
							for he prayed with fervour.
						-
					-
						Mandala 5: Hymn 2: Verse 7: Line 2
					-
						-
							So, Agni, loose from us the bonds that bind us, when thou art seated
							here, O Priest who knowest.
						-
				-
					Mandala 5: Hymn 2: Verse 8
				-
					-
						Mandala 5: Hymn 2: Verse 8: Line 1
					-
						-
							Thou hast sped from me, Agni, in thine anger: this the protector of
							Gods' Laws hath told me.
