					Mandala 5: Hymn 2: Verse 10
				-
					-
						Mandala 5: Hymn 2: Verse 10: Line 1
					-
						-
							Loud in the heaven above be Agni's roarings with keen-edged weapons to
							destroy the demons.
						-
					-
						Mandala 5: Hymn 2: Verse 10: Line 2
					-
						-
							Forth burst his splendours in the Soma's rapture. The godless bands
							press round but cannot stayhim.
						-
				-
					Mandala 5: Hymn 2: Verse 11
				-
					-
						Mandala 5: Hymn 2: Verse 11: Line 1
					-
						-
							As a skilled craftsman makes a car, a singer I, Mighty One! this hymn
							for thee have fashioned.
						-
					-
						Mandala 5: Hymn 2: Verse 11: Line 2
					-
						-
							If thou, O Agni, God, accept it gladly, may we obtain thereby the
							heavenly Waters.
						-
