				Mandala 6: Hymn 22
			-
				-
					Mandala 6: Hymn 22: Verse 1
				-
					-
						Mandala 6: Hymn 22: Verse 1: Line 1
					-
						-
							WITH these my hymns I glorify that Indra who is alone to be invoked by
							mortals,
						-
					-
						Mandala 6: Hymn 22: Verse 1: Line 2
					-
						-
							The Lord, the Mighty One, of manly vigour, victorious, Hero, true, and
							full of wisdom.
						-
				-
					Mandala 6: Hymn 22: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 6: Hymn 22: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							Our sires of old,. Navagvas, sages seven, while urging him to show his
							might, extolled him,
						-
					-
						Mandala 6: Hymn 22: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							Dwelling on heights, swift, smiting down opponents, guileless in word,
							and in his thoughts most mighty.
						-
				-
					Mandala 6: Hymn 22: Verse 3
				-
					-
						Mandala 6: Hymn 22: Verse 3: Line 1
					-
						-
							We seek that Indra to obtain his riches that bring much food, and men,
							and store of heroes.
						-
					-
						Mandala 6: Hymn 22: Verse 3: Line 2
					-
						-
							Bring us, Lord of Bay Steeds, to make us joyful, celestial wealth,
