				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 11: Line 1
					-
						-
							Our maladies have lost their strength and vanished: they feared, and
							passed away into the darkness.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 11: Line 2
					-
						-
							Soma hath risen in us, exceeding mighty, and we are come where men
							prolong existence.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 12
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 12: Line 1
					-
						-
							Fathers, that Indu which our hearts have drunken, Immortal in himself,
							hath entered mortals.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 12: Line 2
					-
						-
							So let us serve this Soma with oblation, and rest securely in his grace
							and favour.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 13
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 13: Line 1
					-
						-
							Associate with the Fathers thou, O Soma, hast spread thyself abroad
							through earth and heaven.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 13: Line 2
					-
						-
							So with oblation let us serve thee, Indu, and so let us become the
							lords of riches,
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 14
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 14: Line 1
					-
						-
							Give us your blessing, O ye Gods' preservers. Never may sleep or idle
							talk control us.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 14: Line 2
					-
						-
							But evermore may we, as friends of Soma, speak to the synod with brave
							sons around us.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 15
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 15: Line 1
					-
						-
							On all sides,. Soma, thou art our life-giver: aim of all eyes,
							light-finder, come within us.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 48: Verse 15: Line 2
					-
						-
							Indu, of one accord with thy protections both from behind and from
							before preserve us.
						-
			-
				Mandala 8: Hymn 49
			-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 1
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 1: Line 1
					-
						-
							AGNI, come hither with thy fires; we choose thee as Invoking Priest.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 1: Line 2
					-
						-
							Let the extended ladle full of oil balm thee, best Priest, to sit on
							sacred grass.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							For unto thee, O Angiras, O Son of Strength, move ladles in the
							sacrifice.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							To Agni, Child of Force, whose locks drop oil, we seek, foremost in
							sacrificial rites.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 3
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 3: Line 1
					-
						-
							Agni, thou art Disposer, Sage, Herald, bright God! and worshipful,
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 3: Line 2
					-
						-
							Best offercr, cheerful, to be praised in holy rites, pure Lord! by
							singers with their hymns.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 4
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 4: Line 1
					-
						-
							Most Youthful and Eternal, bring the longing Gods to me, the guileless,
							for the feast.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 4: Line 2
					-
						-
							Come, Vasu, to the banquet that is well-prepared: rejoice thee,
							gracious, with our songs.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 5
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 5: Line 1
					-
						-
							Famed art thou, Agni, far and wide, Preserver, righteous, and a Sage.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 5: Line 2
					-
						-
							The holy singers, O refulgent kindled God! arrangers, call on thee to
							come -
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 6
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 6: Line 1
					-
						-
							Shine, Most Resplendent! blaze, send bliss unto the folk, and to thy
							worshipper
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 6: Line 2
					-
						-
							Great art thou.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 6: Line 3
					-
						-
							So may my princes, with good fires, subduing foes, rest in the keeping
							of the Gods.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 7
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 7: Line 1
					-
						-
							O Agni, as thou burnest down to earth even high-grown underwood,
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 7: Line 2
					-
						-
							So, bright as Mitra is, burn him who injures us, him who plots ill
							against thy friend.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 8
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 8: Line 1
					-
						-
							Give us not as a prey to mortal enemy, nor to the wicked friend of
							fiends.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 8: Line 2
					-
						-
							With conquering guards, auspicious, unassailable, protect us, O Most
							Youthful God.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 9
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 9: Line 1
					-
						-
							Protect us, Agni, through the first, protect us through the second
							hymn,
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 9: Line 2
					-
						-
							Protect us through three hymns, O Lord of Power and Might, through four
							hymns, Vasu, guard thou us.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 10
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 10: Line 1
					-
						-
							Preserve us from each fiend who brings the Gods no gift, preserve thou
							us in deeds of strength:
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 10: Line 2
					-
						-
							For we possess in thee the nearest Friend of all, for service of the
							Gods and weal.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 11
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 11: Line 1
					-
						-
							O Holy Agni, give us wealth renowned with men and strengthening life.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 11: Line 2
					-
						-
							Bestow on us, O Helper, that which many crave, more glorious still by
							righteousness;
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 12
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 12: Line 1
					-
						-
							Wherewith we may o'ercome our rivals in the war, o'erpowering the foe's
							designs.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 12: Line 2
					-
						-
							So wax thou by our food, O Excellent in strength. Quicken our thoughts
							that find out wealth.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 13
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 13: Line 1
					-
						-
							Agni is even as a bull who whets and brandishes his horns.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 13: Line 2
					-
						-
							Well-sharpened are his jaws which may not be withstood: the Child of
							Strength hath powerful teeth.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 14
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 14: Line 1
					-
						-
							Not to be stayed, O Bull, O Agni, are thy teeth when thou art spreading
							far and wide.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 14: Line 2
					-
						-
							Make our ohlations duly offired up, O Priest, and give us store of
							precious things.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 15
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 15: Line 1
					-
						-
							Thou liest in the wood: from both thy Mothers mortals kindle thee.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 15: Line 2
					-
						-
							Unweariedly thou bearest up the offerer's gifts, then shinest bright
							among the Gods.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 16
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 16: Line 1
					-
						-
							And so the seven priests, O Agni, worship thee, Free-giver, Everlasting
							One.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 16: Line 2
					-
						-
							Thou cIeavest through the rock with heat and fervent glow. Agni, rise
							up above the men.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 17
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 17: Line 1
					-
						-
							For you let us whose grass is trimmed call Agni, Agni, restless God.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 17: Line 2
					-
						-
							Let us whose food is offered call to all the tribes Agni the Invoking
							Priest of men.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 18
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 18: Line 1
					-
						-
							Agni, with noble psalm that tells his wish he dwells, thinking on thee
							who guardest him.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 18: Line 2
					-
						-
							Speedily bring us strength of many varied sorts to be most near to
							succour us.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 19
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 19: Line 1
					-
						-
							Agni, Praise-singer! Lord of men, God burner-up of Raksasas,
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 19: Line 2
					-
						-
							Mighty art thou, the ever-present Household-Lord, Home-friend and
							Guardian from the sky.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 20
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 20: Line 1
					-
						-
							Let no fiend come among us, O thou rich in light, no spell of those who
							deal in spells.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 49: Verse 20: Line 2
					-
						-
							To distant pastures drive faint hunger: far away, O Agni, chase the
							demons' friends.
						-
			-
				Mandala 8: Hymn 50
			-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 1
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 1: Line 1
					-
						-
							BOTH boons,-may Indra, hitherward turned, listen to this prayer of
							ours,
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 1: Line 2
					-
						-
							And mightiest Maghavan with thought inclined to us come near to drink
							the Soma juice.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							For him, strong, independent Ruler, Heaven and Earth have fashioned
							forth for power and might.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							Thou seatest thee as first among thy peers in place, for thy soul longs
							for Soma juice.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 3
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 3: Line 1
					-
						-
							Fill thyself full, O Lord of wealth, O Indra, with the juice we shed.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 3: Line 2
					-
						-
							We know thee, Lord of Bay Steeds victor in the fight, vanquishing e'en
							the invincible.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 4
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 4: Line 1
					-
						-
							Changeless in truth, O Maghavan Indra, let it be as thou in wisdom
							willest it.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 4: Line 2
					-
						-
							May we, O fair of check, win booty with thine aid, O Thunderer, swiftly
							seeking it.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 5
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 5: Line 1
					-
						-
							Indra, with all thy saving helps give us assistance, Lord of power.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 5: Line 2
					-
						-
							For after thee we follow even as glorious bliss, thee, Hero, finder-out
							of wealth.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 6
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 6: Line 1
					-
						-
							Increaser of our steeds and multiplying kine, a golden well, O God, art
							thou,
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 6: Line 2
					-
						-
							For no one may impair the gifts laid up in thee. Bring me whatever
							thing I ask.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 7
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 7: Line 1
					-
						-
							For thou,-come to the worshipper!-wilt find great wealth to make us
							rich.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 7: Line 2
					-
						-
							Fill thyself full, O Maghavan, for gain of kine, full, Indra, for the
							gain of steeds.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 8
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 8: Line 1
					-
						-
							Thou as thy gift bestowest many hundred herds, yea, many thousands dost
							thou give.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 8: Line 2
					-
						-
							With singers' hymns have we brought the Fort-render near, singing to
							Indra for his grace.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 9
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 9: Line 1
					-
						-
							Whether the simple or the sage, Indra, have offered praise to thee,
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 9: Line 2
					-
						-
							He Satakratu! by his love hath gladdened thee, ambitious! ever pressing
							on!
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 10
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 10: Line 1
					-
						-
							If he the Strong of arm, the breaker-down of forts, the great
							Destroyer, hear my call,
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 10: Line 2
					-
						-
							We, seeking riches cry to Indra, Lord of wealth, to Satakratu with our
							lauds.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 11
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 11: Line 1
					-
						-
							We count not then as sinners, nor as niggardly or foolish men,
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 11: Line 2
					-
						-
							When with the Soma juice which we have shed we make Indra, the Mighty
							One, our Friend.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 12
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 12: Line 1
					-
						-
							Him have we yoked in fight, the powerful Conqueror, debt-claimer, not
							to be deceived.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 12: Line 2
					-
						-
							Best charioteer, the Victor marks each fault, he knows the strong to
							whom he will come near.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 13
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 13: Line 1
					-
						-
							Indra, give us security from that whereof we are afraid.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 13: Line 2
					-
						-
							Help us, O Maghavan, let thy succour give us this: drive away foes and
							enemies.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 14
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 14: Line 1
					-
						-
							For thou, O liberal Lord of bounty, strengthenest his ample home who
							worships thee.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 14: Line 2
					-
						-
							So Indra, Maghavan, thou Lover of the Song, we with pressed Soma call
							on thee,
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 15
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 15: Line 1
					-
						-
							Indra is Vrtra-slayer, guard, our best defender from the foe.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 15: Line 2
					-
						-
							May he preserve our last and middlemost, and keep watch from behind us
							and before.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 16
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 16: Line 1
					-
						-
							Defend us from behind, below, above, in front, on all sides, Indra,
							shield us well.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 16: Line 2
					-
						-
							Keep far away from us the terror sent from heaven: keep impious weapons
							far away.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 17
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 17: Line 1
					-
						-
							Protect us, Indra, each to-day, each morrow, and each following day.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 17: Line 2
					-
						-
							Our singers, through all days, shalt thou, Lord of the brave, keep
							safely both by day and night.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 18
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 18: Line 1
					-
						-
							A crushing Warrior, passing rich is Maghavan, endowed with all heroic
							might.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 50: Verse 18: Line 2
					-
						-
							Thine arms, O Satakratu, are exceeding strong, arms which have grasped
							the thunderbolt.
						-
			-
				Mandala 8: Hymn 51
			-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 1
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 1: Line 1
					-
						-
							OFFER ye up as praise to him that wherein Indra takes delight.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 1: Line 2
					-
						-
							The Soma-bringers magnify Indra's great energy with hymns. Good are the
							gifts that Indra gives.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							Sole among chiefs, companionless, impetuous, and peerless, he
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							Hath waxen great o'er many folk, yea., over all things born, in might.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 3
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 3: Line 1
					-
						-
							Lord of swift bounty, he will win e'en with a steed of worthless sort.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 3: Line 2
					-
						-
							This, Indra, must be told of thee who wilt perform heroic deeds.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 4
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 4: Line 1
					-
						-
							Come to us.hither: let us pay devotions that enhance thy might,
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 4: Line 2
					-
						-
							For which, Most Potent! thou wouldst fain bless the man here who
							strives for fame.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 5
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 5: Line 1
					-
						-
							For thou, O Indra, makest yet more bold the spirit of the bold
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 5: Line 2
					-
						-
							Who with strong Soma serveth thee, still ready with his reverent
							prayers.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 6
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 6: Line 1
					-
						-
							Worthy of song, he looketh down as a man looketh into wells.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 6: Line 2
					-
						-
							Pleased with the Soma-bringer's skill he maketh him his mate and
							friend.
						-
				-
					Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 7
				-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 7: Line 1
					-
						-
							In strength and wisdom all the Gods, Indra, have yielded unto thee.
						-
					-
						Mandala 8: Hymn 51: Verse 7: Line 2
