							They harness to the broad-wheeled car the mighty Courser whose back
							bears meath, unwearied, awful.
						-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 89: Verse 4: Line 2
					-
						-
							The twins, the sisters brighten him, and strengthen-these children of
							one damethe vigorous Racer.
						-
				-
					Mandala 9: Hymn 89: Verse 5
				-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 89: Verse 5: Line 1
					-
						-
							Four pouring out the holy oil attend him, sitting together in the same
							container.
						-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 89: Verse 5: Line 2
					-
						-
							To him they flow, when purified, with homage, and still, from every
							side, are first about him.
						-
				-
					Mandala 9: Hymn 89: Verse 6
				-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 89: Verse 6: Line 1
					-
						-
							He is the buttress of the heavens, supporter of earth, and in his hand
							are all the people.
						-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 89: Verse 6: Line 2
					-
						-
							Be the team's Lord a well to thee the singer: cleansed is the sweet
							plant's stalk for deed of glory.
						-
				-
					Mandala 9: Hymn 89: Verse 7
				-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 89: Verse 7: Line 1
					-
						-
							Fighting, uninjured come where Gods are feasted; Soma, as Vitra-slayer
							flow for Indra.
						-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 89: Verse 7: Line 2
					-
						-
							Vouchsafe us ample riches very splendid may we be masters of heroic
							vigour.
						-
			-
				Mandala 9: Hymn 90
			-
				-
					Mandala 9: Hymn 90: Verse 1
				-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 90: Verse 1: Line 1
					-
						-
							URGED On, the Father of the Earth and Heaven hath gone forth like a car
