				Mandala 9: Hymn 94
			-
				-
					Mandala 9: Hymn 94: Verse 1
				-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 94: Verse 1: Line 1
					-
						-
							WHEN beauties strive for him as for a charger, then strive the songs
							like soldiers for the sunlight.
						-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 94: Verse 1: Line 2
					-
						-
							Acting the Sage, he flows enrobed in waters and song as 'twere a stall
							that kine may prosper.
						-
				-
					Mandala 9: Hymn 94: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 94: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							The worlds expand to hirn who from aforetime found light to spread the
							law of life eternal.
						-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 94: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							The swelling songs, like kine within the stable, in deep devotion call
							aloud on Indu.
						-
				-
					Mandala 9: Hymn 94: Verse 3
				-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 94: Verse 3: Line 1
					-
						-
							When the sage bears his holy wisdom round him, like a car visiting all
							worlds, the Hero,
						-
					-
						Mandala 9: Hymn 94: Verse 3: Line 2
					-
						-
							Becoming fame, mid Gods, unto the mortal, wealth to the skilled, worth
							praise mid the Ever-present,
