					Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 7
				-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 7: Line 1
					-
						-
							Him of a thousand powers, subduing foemen, Maghavan praised with hymns
							and pleased with Soma,-
						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 7: Line 2
					-
						-
							Even him our songs approach, resistless Indra: the adorations of the
							singer laud him.
						-
				-
					Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 8
				-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 8: Line 1
					-
						-
							The way to bliss for Gods and man thou foundest, Indra, seven lovely
							floods, divine, untroubled,
						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 8: Line 2
					-
						-
							Wherewith thou, rending forts, didst move the ocean, and
							nine-and-ninety flowing streams of water.
						-
