					Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 9
				-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 9: Line 1
					-
						-
							Thou from the curse didst free the mighty Waters, and as their only God
							didst watch and guard them.
						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 9: Line 2
					-
						-
							O Indra, cherish evermore thy body with those which thou hast won in
							quelling Vrtra.
						-
				-
					Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 10
				-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 10: Line 1
					-
						-
							Heroic power and noble praise is Indra yea, the song worships him
							invoked of many.
						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 104: Verse 10: Line 2
					-
						-
							Vrtra he quelled, and gave men room and freedom: gakra, victorious,
							hath conquered armies.
						-
