					Mandala 10: Hymn 134: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 134: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							Relax that mortal's stubborn strength whose heart is bent on
							wickedness.
						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 134: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							Trample him down beneath thy feet who watches for and aims at us. The
							Goddess Mother brought thee forth, the Blessed Mother gave thee life.
						-
				-
					Mandala 10: Hymn 134: Verse 3
				-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 134: Verse 3: Line 1
					-
						-
							Shake down, O Slayer of the foe, those great all splendid enemies.
						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 134: Verse 3: Line 2
					-
						-
							With all thy powers, O Sakra, all thine helps, O Indra, shake them
