				Mandala 10: Hymn 135
			-
				-
					Mandala 10: Hymn 135: Verse 1
				-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 135: Verse 1: Line 1
					-
						-
							IN the Tree clothed with goodly leaves where Yama drinketh with the
							Gods,
						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 135: Verse 1: Line 2
					-
						-
							The Father, Master of the house, tendeth with love our ancient Sires.
						-
				-
					Mandala 10: Hymn 135: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 135: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							I looked reluctantly on him who cherishes those men of old,
						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 135: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							On him who treads that evil path, and then I yearned for this again.
						-
				-
					Mandala 10: Hymn 135: Verse 3
				-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 135: Verse 3: Line 1
					-
						-
							Thou mountest, though thou dost not see, O Child, the new and
							wheel-less car
						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 135: Verse 3: Line 2
					-
						-
							Which thou hast fashioned mentally, onepoled but turning every way.
