						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 136: Verse 1: Line 2
					-
						-
							He is all sky to look upon: he with long hair is called this light.
						-
				-
					Mandala 10: Hymn 136: Verse 2
				-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 136: Verse 2: Line 1
					-
						-
							The Munis, girdled with the wind, wear garments soiled of yellow hue.
						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 136: Verse 2: Line 2
					-
						-
							They, following the wind's swift course go where the Gods have gone
							before.
						-
				-
					Mandala 10: Hymn 136: Verse 3
				-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 136: Verse 3: Line 1
					-
						-
							Transported with our Munihood we have pressed on into the winds:
						-
					-
						Mandala 10: Hymn 136: Verse 3: Line 2
					-
						-
							You therefore, mortal men. behold our natural bodies and no more.
						-
